# Wellfit QA — Jira STAGE completion comment (short format)

When **STAGE QA is done** (or Chris asks for the Jira comment), give this **short English** block **ready to copy/paste into Jira**. Do it at ticket close together with the chat verdict — do **not** wait for him to ask again. Do **not** include QA engineer name unless they ask.

The Jira comment **is** a fenced copy block. The internal QA verdict in chat is **not** (see `wellfit-qa-ticket-verdict.mdc`).

## Template

```text
STAGE QA PASS — {TICKET-ID}.

{Setup: 1–2 sentences — test data, failure trigger or main action, HTTP trigger if API.}

Verified: {comma-separated pass bullets — alerts, DB state, service health, logs. Note expected secondary signals (e.g. coordinator email) as "expected", not defects.}

Recovery: {if run — restore step, re-trigger outcome, synthetic caveats. Omit section if N/A.}

{Out-of-scope ACs}: unit tests {PR if known}. Evidence in Testmo.
```

## Rules

- **Language:** English (Jira / US client).
- **Tone:** factual, compact — no long paragraphs.
- **Result line:** start with `STAGE QA PASS — {TICKET-ID}.` (use `FAIL` / `BLOCKED` only if that was the outcome).
- **Evidence:** point to **Testmo**; do not paste screenshots into Jira unless asked.
- **Synthetic data:** call out NULL timestamps / 404 file-not-found when rows have no real files.
- **Merged behavior:** name related tickets when a second email or signal is expected (e.g. PAY-3587 coordinator).

## Example (PAY-3821)

```text
STAGE QA PASS — PAY-3821.

Synthetic setup: 3 pending FundingBatches (PAY3821-E2E-*), SFTP broken via sftpurl=10.255.255.1, trigger POST /send-funding-batch → 202.

Verified: one PAY-3821 alert listing all 3 unsent batches; rows stayed NULL; service healthy (202/health); App Insights SFTP failure logged. Coordinator stage-failed email also received (expected PAY-3587).

Recovery: restored sftpurl to batch.vantivprelive.com, re-trigger → rows re-attempted, NULL retained (synthetic), error changed to storage 404 — AC-5 pass. Cleanup done.

AC-4 + sent-before exclusion: unit tests PR #283. Evidence in Testmo.
```
